Centres%20(MCCs)%2C%20facilitating%20direct%20interactions%20between%20job%20seekers%20and%20Amazon's%20recruitment%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnion%20Minister%20of%20Labour%20and%20Employment%20Mansukh%20Mandaviya%20stated%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20NCS%20portal%20is%20evolving%20into%20a%20one-stop%20platform%20for%20accessing%20employment%20opportunities%20across%20sectors%20and%20industries.%20This%20portal%20is%20a%20game%20changer%20for%20young%20job%20seekers%2C%20offering%20them%20various%20employment-related%20services%20under%20one%20roof.%20Through%20our%20partnership%20with%20Amazon%2C%20we%20are%20expanding%20job%20accessibility%20for%20India's%20youth%2C%20empowering%20them%20to%20discover%20the%20right%20roles%20and%20build%20a%20future%20filled%20with%20opportunities%20and%20growth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmphasising%20the%20initiative's%20focus%20on%20inclusivity%2C%20Mr%20Mandaviya%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20upgrading%20the%20NCS%20portal%20to%20provide%20a%20more%20user-friendly%20interface%2C%20utilising%20advanced%20technologies%20like%20artificial%20intelligence%20to%20enhance%20the%20experience%20for%20job%20seekers%2C%20employers%2C%20and%20stakeholders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnion%20Minister%20Sushri%20Karandlaje%20remarked%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20National%20Career%20Service%20portal%20acts%20as%20a%20dynamic%20bridge%20connecting%20India's%20diverse%20talent%20pool%20with%20opportunities%20across%20sectors.%20When%20integrated%20with%20an%20ecosystem%20like%20Amazon%2C%20it%20will%20foster%20skill%20development%2C%20empower%20individuals%2C%20and%20promote%20economic%20growth%20and%20job%20creation.%20The%20integration%20with%20a%20centralized%20platform%20like%20NCS%20will%20reduce%20hiring%20costs%20and%20time%20while%20streamlining%20the%20hiring%20of%20verified%20professionals.%20This%20is%20a%20step%20forward%20for%20economic%20inclusion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKey%20Points%20Of%20The%20Collaboration%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EJob%20Postings%3A%20Amazon%20will%20regularly%20post%20job%20vacancies%20on%20the%20NCS%20portal%20and%20conduct%20hiring%20through%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EJob%20Fairs%3A%20The%20initiative%20will%20include%20job%20fairs%20at%20Model%20Career%20Centres%2C%20providing%20opportunities%20for%20direct%20interaction%20with%20Amazon's%20recruitment%20teams.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EInclusivity%20Focus%3A%20The%20partnership%20prioritises%20employment%20opportunities%20for%20women%20and%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20ensuring%20equal%20access.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBenefits%20To%20Job%20Seekers%20On%20The%20NCS%20Portal%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJob%20seekers%20will%20have%20access%20to%20a%20broader%20range%20of%20opportunities%2C%20particularly%20in%20logistics%2C%20technology%2C%20and%20customer%20service%20through%20Amazon%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20e-commerce%20companies.%20This%20MoU%20not%20only%20facilitates%20local%20hiring%20but%20also%20offers%20career%20advancement%20opportunities%20within%20a%20prestigious%20organization.%20Consequently%2C%20job%20seekers%20from%20various%20regions%20of%20India%20can%20connect%20with%20numerous%20employment%20roles%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20brighter%20futures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBenefits%20To%20Amazon%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20this%20collaboration%2C%20Amazon%20aims%20to%20tap%20into%20a%20diverse%20talent%20pool%20via%20the%20NCS%20portal%2C%20which%20includes%20women%20and%20persons%20with%20disabilities.%20The%20Ministry%20will%20support%20Amazon%20by%20integrating%20databases%20to%20ensure%20seamless%20access%20to%20candidates%20through%20an%20efficient%20technology%20interface.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20Ministry%20will%20assist%20in%20conducting%20job%20fairs%20nationwide%2C%20facilitating%20structured%20interactions%20with%20potential%20employees%20to%20help%20Amazon%20meet%20its%20staffing%20needs%20while%20promoting%20a%20diverse%20and%20inclusive%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENCS%20Portal%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaunched%20in%20July%202015%2C%20the%20National%20Career%20Service%20(NCS)%20portal%20has%20transformed%20India's%20employment%20landscape.%20Managed%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Labour%20%26amp%3B%20Employment%2C%20the%20portal%20provides%20essential%20services%20such%20as%20job%20searches%2C%20career%20counselling%2C%20vocational%20guidance%2C%20and%20skill%20development%20resources.%20It%20serves%20millions%2C%20including%20job%20seekers%2C%20employers%2C%20and%20educational%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20the%20NCS%20portal%20celebrated%20a%20milestone%20by%20surpassing%202%20million%20active%20vacancies%20in%20a%20single%20day%2C%20with%20an%20average%20of%2015-18%20lakh%20job%20opportunities%20listed%20at%20any%20time.%20Currently%2C%20the%20platform%20boasts%20over%2060%20lakh%20active%20job%20seekers%20and%2033.5%20lakh%20active%20employers%2C%20making%20it%20a%20vital%20tool%20in%20bridging%20the%20gap%20between%20talent%20and%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NCS%20portal%20is%20integrated%20with%20employment%20portals%20from%2028%20states%20and%20union%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727429160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fsl2rir3_ministry-of-labour-employment-mous-with-amazon_625x300_27_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Feducation%2Fministry-of-labour-partners-with-amazon-to-enhance-job-opportunities-6662092%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20two-year%20Memorandum%20of%20Understanding%20(MoU)%20allows%20Amazon%20and%20its%20third-party%20staffing%20agencies%20to%20regularly%20post%20job%20openings%20on%20the%20National%20Career%20Service%20(NCS)%20portal.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Feducation%2Fministry-of-labour-partners-with-amazon-to-enhance-job-opportunities-6662092%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20How%20Bengal%2C%20Once%20An%20Economic%20Powerhouse%2C%20Lost%20Its%20Shine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fw.ndtvimg.com%2Fdomain%2F3%2F2017%2F02%2F28102106%2FBengal-Civic-Bodies-To-Build-1.5-Lakh-More-Toilets-Across-3-Districts.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWest%20Bengal%2C%20once%20a%20dominant%20player%20in%20India's%20economy%2C%20has%20seen%20a%20consistent%20decline%20in%20both%20its%20share%20of%20India's%20GDP%20and%20its%20relative%20per%20capita%20income%20over%20the%20past%20six%20decades.%20In%201960-61%2C%20West%20Bengal%20contributed%2010.5%25%20to%20the%20national%20GDP%2C%20ranking%20third%20among%20Indian%20states%2C%20but%20this%20share%20has%20shrunk%20significantly%20to%205.6%25%20in%202023-24%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Statistics%20and%20Programme%20Implementation%20(MoSPI).%20The%20data%20has%20been%20collated%20in%20a%20working%20paper%20by%20the%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20by%20Sanjeev%20Sanyal%20%26amp%3B%20Aakanksha%20Arora.%20This%20decline%20is%20even%20more%20evident%20in%20terms%20of%20per%20capita%20income.%20Once%20boasting%20a%20per%20capita%20income%20127.5%25%20of%20the%20national%20average%2C%20West%20Bengal%20now%20sits%20at%20only%2083.7%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWest%20Bengal's%20economic%20decline%2C%20particularly%20in%20comparison%20to%20its%20counterparts%20Maharashtra%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20reflects%20a%20marked%20divergence%20in%20growth%20trajectories%20since%20the%201960s.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20independence%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20along%20with%20Maharashtra%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20was%20an%20industrial%20powerhouse%2C%20with%20Calcutta%20being%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20industrial%20clusters%20in%20the%20country.%20However%2C%20while%20Maharashtra%20maintained%20its%20economic%20standing%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20surged%20after%20the%201991%20liberalisation%2C%20West%20Bengal's%20decline%20began%20as%20early%20as%20the%201960s.%20The%20state's%20share%20in%20India's%20GDP%20fell%20from%2010.5%25%20in%201960-61%20to%20a%20mere%205.6%25%20by%202023-24%2C%20the%20sharpest%20drop%20among%20all%20states.%20This%20decline%20persisted%20even%20after%20economic%20liberalisation%2C%20which%20benefited%20other%20regions.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20West%20Bengal's%20industrial%20and%20economic%20prominence%20has%20significantly%20eroded%2C%20leaving%20it%20lagging%20behind%20its%20former%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Share%20of%20Maharashtra%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20West%20Bengal%20in%20India's%20GDP%20(Source%3A%20EAC-PM%20Working%20Paper)%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Share%20of%20Maharashtra%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20West%20Bengal%20in%20India's%20GDP%20(Source%3A%20EAC-PM%20Working%20Paper)%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fd5djs2r8_bengal-1_625x300_27_September_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShare%20of%20Maharashtra%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20West%20Bengal%20in%20India's%20GDP%20(Source%3A%20EAC-PM%20Working%20Paper)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20Odisha%2C%20a%20state%20that%20historically%20lagged%20behind%20in%20most%20economic%20indicators%2C%20has%20undergone%20a%20significant%20transformation.%20From%20a%20relative%20per%20capita%20income%20of%2054.3%25%20in%201990-91%2C%20Odisha%20now%20stands%20at%2088.5%25%20in%202023-24%2C%20a%20remarkable%20turnaround%20that%20highlights%20the%20divergent%20paths%20of%20the%20two%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Relative%20per%20capita%20income%20of%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Odisha%20and%20Assam.%20(Source%3A%20EAC-PM%20Working%20Paper)%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Relative%20per%20capita%20income%20of%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Odisha%20and%20Assam.%20(Source%3A%20EAC-PM%20Working%20Paper)%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fg99s79oo_bengal_625x300_27_September_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERelative%20per%20capita%20income%20of%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Odisha%20and%20Assam.%20(Source%3A%20EAC-PM%20Working%20Paper)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20difference%20between%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Odisha%20lies%20in%20their%20respective%20responses%20to%20national%20economic%20reforms%2C%20particularly%20those%20initiated%20in%201991.%20While%20West%20Bengal%20failed%20to%20capitalise%20on%20liberalisation%2C%20Odisha%20took%20full%20advantage%20of%20these%20changes%20to%20spur%20growth.%20Studies%20such%20as%20Ahluwalia's%20(2000)%20and%20the%20OECD's%20report%20on%20India's%20regional%20development%20(2014)%20attribute%20West%20Bengal's%20decline%20to%20policy%20inertia%2C%20a%20challenging%20business%20environment%2C%20and%20rigid%20labour%20laws.%20The%20state%2C%20known%20for%20its%20historically%20militant%20trade%20unions%20and%20restrictive%20labour%20regulations%2C%20deterred%20private%20investment%2C%20especially%20in%20manufacturing%20and%20industry.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Odisha%20pursued%20a%20series%20of%20reforms%20to%20improve%20its%20business%20climate.%20As%20noted%20in%20a%202019%20NITI%20Aayog%20report%2C%20Odisha%20made%20strides%20in%20ease%20of%20doing%20business%20by%20simplifying%20regulations%2C%20improving%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20actively%20courting%20foreign%20and%20domestic%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Odisha%20Turned%20Its%20Fate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOdisha's%20success%20can%20be%20traced%20to%20its%20focus%20on%20industrial%20development%2C%20infrastructure%20investment%2C%20and%20governance%20reforms%2C%20particularly%20after%20the%20early%202000s.%20The%20state%20implemented%20several%20proactive%20policies%20to%20attract%20investment%20in%20sectors%20such%20as%20mining%2C%20steel%2C%20and%20manufacturing.%20According%20to%20a%20World%20Bank%20report%20on%20Indian%20states%20(2017)%2C%20Odisha's%20government%20focused%20on%20creating%20investor-friendly%20policies%2C%20reducing%20red%20tape%2C%20and%20modernising%20its%20industrial%20policies%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20attracted%20major%20players%20like%20Tata%20Steel%20and%20Vedanta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20reforms%2C%20combined%20with%20improvements%20in%20connectivity%20and%20infrastructure%2C%20helped%20Odisha's%20economy%20grow%20at%20a%20faster%20pace%20than%20its%20peers%2C%20including%20West%20Bengal.%20Odisha's%20share%20in%20India's%20GDP%2C%20while%20still%20modest%2C%20has%20increased%2C%20and%20its%20per%20capita%20income%20has%20grown%20steadily.%20West%20Bengal%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20has%20seen%20its%20industrial%20base%20erode%2C%20with%20key%20industries%20like%20jute%20and%20textiles%20failing%20to%20modernise%2C%20leading%20to%20stagnation%20in%20both%20output%20and%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWest%20Bengal%20And%20Odisha%3A%20Two%20Different%20Trajectories%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20divergence%20in%20economic%20trajectories%20between%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Odisha%20is%20also%20reflected%20in%20social%20and%20human%20development%20indicators.%20According%20to%20the%20multidimensional%20poverty%20index%2C%20Odisha%20has%20made%20significant%20improvements%20in%20literacy%2C%20life%20expectancy%2C%20and%20poverty%20reduction%2C%20driven%20by%20its%20economic%20growth%20and%20targeted%20welfare%20programmes.%20West%20Bengal%2C%20while%20performing%20relatively%20well%20in%20literacy%20and%20health%20metrics%2C%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20convert%20these%20into%20sustained%20economic%20gains.%20Odisha's%20focus%20on%20inclusive%20growth%2C%20particularly%20its%20emphasis%20on%20poverty%20alleviation%20programmes%2C%20has%20resulted%20in%20significant%20reductions%20in%20poverty%20rates%2C%20from%2057%25%20in%202004-05%20to%2032%25%20in%202011-12%2C%20as%20per%20Planning%20Commission%20data.%20In%20contrast%2C%20West%20Bengal's%20poverty%20reduction%20has%20been%20more%20sluggish%2C%20with%20entrenched%20rural%20poverty%20remaining%20a%20challenge%20despite%20various%20government%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20may%20come%20up%20with%20the%20headcount%20ratio%20once%20the%20HCES%20data%20is%20fully%20released.%20However%2C%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20this%20data%2C%20the%20Multidimensional%20Poverty%20Index%20offers%20insights%20into%20poverty%20levels.%20A%20closer%20examination%20of%20the%20state-wise%20percentage%20point%20change%20in%20headcount%20ratio%20between%202015-16%20and%202019-21%20reveals%20a%20stark%20contrast%3A%20Odisha%20saw%20a%20significant%20decline%20of%2013.68%25%2C%20whereas%20West%20Bengal's%20reduction%20was%20only%209.41%25.%20This%20disparity%20highlights%20how%20West%20Bengal's%20progress%20in%20reducing%20poverty%20has%20lagged%20behind%2C%20even%20when%20compared%20to%20Odisha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBengal's%20Reliance%20On%20Agriculture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20critical%20factors%20in%20Odisha's%20success%20has%20been%20its%20ability%20to%20transition%20from%20an%20agrarian%20economy%20to%20an%20industrial%20one%2C%20while%20West%20Bengal%20has%20remained%20overly%20dependent%20on%20agriculture.%20As%20per%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India's%20'Handbook%20of%20Statistics%20on%20Indian%20States'%20(2022)%2C%20the%20share%20of%20agriculture%20in%20Odisha's%20Gross%20State%20Domestic%20Product%20(GSDP)%20declined%20from%2037%25%20in%201990-91%20to%20around%2016%25%20in%202020-21%2C%20while%20the%20industrial%20sector's%20share%20increased%20correspondingly.%20This%20shift%20towards%20a%20more%20diversified%20economy%20has%20been%20crucial%20in%20driving%20sustained%20economic%20growth%20in%20Odisha.%20West%20Bengal%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20continues%20to%20rely%20heavily%20on%20agriculture%2C%20which%20remains%20vulnerable%20to%20climatic%20changes%20and%20price%20fluctuations.%20Despite%20being%20an%20early%20leader%20in%20industry%2C%20West%20Bengal's%20industrial%20growth%20has%20stagnated%2C%20with%20the%20state%20failing%20to%20attract%20significant%20new%20investment%20or%20develop%20new%20sectors%20beyond%20traditional%20industries%20like%20jute%20and%20textiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20role%20of%20governance%20and%20political%20stability%20cannot%20be%20ignored%20in%20explaining%20the%20contrasting%20economic%20trajectories.%20Odisha%20has%20experienced%20consistent%20political%20stability%2C%20allowing%20for%20long-term%20planning%20and%20execution%20of%20reforms.%20The%20state%20government%20has%20been%20credited%20with%20reducing%20corruption%2C%20improving%20governance%2C%20and%20implementing%20policies%20that%20foster%20industrial%20growth%20and%20infrastructure%20development.%20In%20contrast%2C%20West%20Bengal's%20political%20landscape%20has%20been%20more%20turbulent%2C%20with%20frequent%20changes%20in%20leadership%20and%20governance%20styles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOdisha's%20Approach%20To%20PPP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20Odisha's%20approach%20to%20public-private%20partnerships%20(PPP)%20in%20infrastructure%20development%20has%20been%20significantly%20more%20successful%20than%20West%20Bengal's.%20As%20per%20the%20Economic%20Survey%20of%20India%20(2021-22)%2C%20Odisha%20has%20successfully%20leveraged%20PPP%20models%20to%20build%20roads%2C%20ports%2C%20and%20industrial%20parks%2C%20which%20have%20further%20fuelled%20industrial%20growth.%20The%20Paradip%20Port%20in%20Odisha%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20has%20become%20a%20major%20hub%20for%20both%20domestic%20and%20international%20trade%2C%20providing%20a%20crucial%20advantage%20for%20industrial%20activities%20in%20the%20state.%20West%20Bengal%2C%20despite%20having%20the%20strategic%20Kolkata%20Port%2C%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20replicate%20such%20success%20due%20to%20inefficiencies%2C%20political%20bottlenecks%2C%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20coordinated%20investment%20in%20infrastructure.%20The%20state's%20inability%20to%20modernise%20its%20port%20and%20transport%20infrastructure%20has%20further%20contributed%20to%20its%20declining%20economic%20relevance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20meaningful%20reforms%2C%20state%20governments%20risk%20failing%20their%20citizens%20by%20allowing%20stagnation%20and%20economic%20decline%20to%20persist.%20West%20Bengal's%20steady%20fall%20from%20an%20industrial%20leader%20to%20a%20state%20with%20diminishing%20GDP%20share%20and%20per%20capita%20income%20exemplifies%20the%20consequences%20of%20policy%20inertia%20and%20poor%20governance.%20In%20contrast%2C%20Odisha's%20proactive%20reforms%2C%20improved%20business%20climate%2C%20and%20strategic%20focus%20on%20infrastructure%20and%20industrial%20growth%20have%20driven%20its%20remarkable%20economic%20transformation.%20If%20states%20like%20West%20Bengal%20do%20not%20prioritise%20structural%20reforms%2C%20enhance%20governance%2C%20and%20diversify%20their%20economies%2C%20they%20will%20continue%20to%20lag%20behind%2C%20failing%20to%20meet%20the%20aspirations%20of%20their%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bibek%20Debroy%20is%20Chairman%2C%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20and%20Aditya%20Sinha%20is%20OSD%2C%20Research%2C%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727428980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fw.ndtvimg.com%2Fdomain%2F3%2F2017%2F02%2F28102106%2FBengal-Civic-Bodies-To-Build-1.5-Lakh-More-Toilets-Across-3-Districts.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhow-bengal-once-a