9%2Fmoringa-2-1727091760-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-367178%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDr%20Saravanan%20dries%20moringa%20leaves%20under%20shade%20before%20processing%20it%20into%20value-added%20products.%C2%A0%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmbracing%20the%20principles%20of%20zero-budget%20natural%20farming%2C%20Dr%20Saravanan%20dedicated%20himself%20to%20promoting%20sustainable%20agriculture%20practices%20that%20not%20only%20enhance%20soil%20health%20but%20also%20uplift%20agriculture%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReturning%20to%20his%20roots%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20he%20chose%20to%20revive%20his%20family%E2%80%99s%20farming%20legacy%20by%20focusing%20on%20cultivating%20moringa%20oleifera%20%E2%80%94%20a%20versatile%20tree%20known%20for%20its%20nutritional%20and%20medicinal%20properties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ERedefining%20moringa%20farming%20with%20sustainable%20practices%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHighlighting%20the%20difference%20between%20farming%20techniques%20for%20harvesting%20drumsticks%20and%20leaves%2C%20Dr%20Saravanan%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20drumstick%20farming%2C%20trees%20are%20planted%20with%20a%20wider%20spacing%20of%2015%20feet%2C%20whereas%20in%20its%20leaves%20cultivation%2C%20saplings%20are%20planted%20closely%20together.%20The%20leaves%20are%20cut%20when%20the%20tree%20reaches%20a%20height%20of%20two%20feet.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20allow%20the%20tree%20to%20flower%2C%20the%20nutrition%20stored%20in%20the%20leaves%20will%20be%20used%20up%20to%20grow%20the%20drumsticks.%20This%20will%20result%20in%20lesser-quality%20leaves.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20I%20harvest%20the%20leaves%20before%20the%20flowering%20phase.%20Also%2C%20you%20can%20harvest%20leaves%20up%20to%20six%20times%20at%2050%20to%2060%20day%20intervals.%20This%20ensures%20year-round%20production%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explain